Abe Forsythe born Abraham Forsythe on the 26 July , 1981 , is anAustralian actor . He is the son of actor / comedian Drew Forsythe . He first appeared on the TV series The Miraculous Mellops . He has since appeared as Campbell Todd on the Australian TV series Always Greener , starred in the mini - series Marking Time and starred and directed the 2003 film Ned . He also directed and starred in a parody of The Matrix called Computer Boy. Forsythe has also recently written a number of acclaimed sketches for the late night sketch comedy series Comedy Inc - The Late Shift . He also stars in the Australian / British television series co - production Tripping Over . Abe Forsythe , has also guest starred in Australian Television Shows , including Blue Heelers , All Saints and Water Rats . 